191
00:13:08,350 --> 00:13:11,470
There's nothing this sword can't cut!

192
00:13:14,130 --> 00:13:17,020
Shinsuke Takasugi. Are you saying he's

193
00:13:17,020 --> 00:13:20,810
the major figure behind Katsura-san's disappearance and Nizo Okada?

194
00:13:20,810 --> 00:13:25,380
While we were looking for Katsura-san, we followed many leads, but...

195
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:29,050
...we never thought we'd find another exclusionist rebel behind his disappearance.

196
00:13:29,050 --> 00:13:33,020
And speaking of Shinsuke Takasugi, he was Katsura-san's old ally,

197
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:37,160
and they fought in the Anti-Foreigner War together. So why would he...?

198
00:13:37,540 --> 00:13:40,910
According to rumors, Takasugi revived the Kiheitai

199
00:13:40,910 --> 00:13:44,470
along with Nizo the Butcher; the gun fighter Matako "Crimson Bullet" Kijima;

200
00:13:44,470 --> 00:13:54,680
that scheming pervert Henpeita Takechi; and the feared swordsman, Bansai Kawakami.

201
00:13:54,680 --> 00:13:56,270
The Kiheitai?

202
00:13:56,270 --> 00:13:59,180
It's a volunteer army led by Takasugi.

203
00:13:59,180 --> 00:14:02,190
It's said they fight like ferocious demons.

204
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:06,530
I also heard that they're secretly developing devastating weapons.

205
00:14:06,530 --> 00:14:11,010
His goal is to most likely form a strong-armed group to launch a coup d'état.

206
00:14:11,860 --> 00:14:13,400
Katsura-san renounced violence

207
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:16,600
and seeks to restore Edo's sovereignty by more peaceful means.

208
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:21,410
Maybe Takasugi was angry with him for his change of heart.

209
00:14:22,610 --> 00:14:25,570
Anyway, we have to do something!

210
00:14:25,570 --> 00:14:28,610
Elizabeth-san, let's attack Takasugi's hideout!!

211
00:14:28,610 --> 00:14:30,260
